<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>press someone’s buttons • press the panic button</xh5><p> <i>press someone’s buttons</i>—(also: push someone’s buttons) draw a strong emotional reaction, especially anger, from a person: It is very difficult to <u>press his buttons</u> because he is careful not to let his emotions control him.</p><p> <i>press the panic button</i>—(also: push the panic button) overreact to a stressful situation: I fail to understand as to why the investors have <u>pressed the panic button</u> at a time when a new Government has not taken over.</p> </entry>
